-Better to be safe than sorry.

28:01.767 --> 28:03.464
Can I--

28:06.946 --> 28:09.731
No one's gonna
recognize you here.

28:09.775 --> 28:12.647
Wow, yeah, what--
where is here?

28:12.691 --> 28:14.388
Why are you staying
in this place?

28:14.431 --> 28:16.390
Uh, it's cheap.

28:16.433 --> 28:18.479
And when your
incestuous infidelity

28:18.522 --> 28:20.133
gets blasted
all over the Internet,

28:20.176 --> 28:23.440
your wife tends to kick you out
and your boss tends to fire you.

28:24.877 --> 28:28.315
Well, that's why married guys
shouldn't be on dating apps.

28:28.358 --> 28:30.317
I know.

28:30.360 --> 28:32.841
It's for single people.

28:32.885 --> 28:34.321
Very single.

28:34.364 --> 28:35.931
You, not single.

28:37.585 --> 28:39.369
You lied to me, Sam.

28:40.806 --> 28:42.590
Really sorry, Julia.

28:42.633 --> 28:44.331
Why'd you do it?

28:44.374 --> 28:46.594
I don't know.

28:46.637 --> 28:49.336
I had a good life.
I had everything.

28:49.379 --> 28:51.642
I deserve this.

28:51.686 --> 28:55.342
Well, I don't know
if I deserve this.

28:55.385 --> 28:57.257
Yeah, so in summary,

28:57.300 --> 28:59.520
we both feel humiliated,

28:59.563 --> 29:01.957
vulnerable, exposed.

29:02.001 --> 29:03.567
Yeah.

29:03.611 --> 29:04.873
When you came to the clinic,

29:04.917 --> 29:07.441
you said we needed
to do something.

29:07.484 --> 29:10.618
So let's do something.

29:13.926 --> 29:15.797
Hey, Nick.

29:15.841 --> 29:18.017
Um, Roxy Doyle.

29:18.060 --> 29:20.846
Hey.
Mitch isn't quite ready yet.

29:20.889 --> 29:22.412
You know,
your mom said she'd be back.

29:22.456 --> 29:24.501
Yeah, I know, but she had--
she had something come up,

29:24.545 --> 29:26.286
and she asked me to grab him.

29:26.329 --> 29:28.854
And I'm kind of
in a hurry, so...

29:28.897 --> 29:30.638
I should probably
just call her to make sure.

29:30.681 --> 29:35.251
You know what?
He looks ready to me, so...

29:35.295 --> 29:37.384
Hey, what're you doing?
You can't be back there.

29:38.428 --> 29:39.429
No!

29:48.874 --> 29:50.005
-DIANE: Hello?
-JULIA: Okay, okay.

29:50.049 --> 29:51.311
-Keep your pants on.
-DIANE: Roxy!

29:51.354 --> 29:53.313
DIANE: I know you're in there.

29:53.356 --> 29:55.184
Roxy!

29:55.228 --> 29:58.187
Oh.

29:58.231 --> 30:00.363
-You must be--
-Roxy's mother.

30:00.407 --> 30:02.017
Right.
I'm Julia.

30:02.061 --> 30:04.237
I know who you are.
Now where's my baby?

30:04.280 --> 30:06.369
She's probably sleeping.

30:06.413 --> 30:08.850
My dog.
Where are you keeping him?

30:08.894 --> 30:09.982
I'm--I'm sorry, Mrs. Doyle.

30:10.025 --> 30:10.983
I don't know
what you're talking about.

30:11.026 --> 30:12.288
There's definitely no dog here.

30:13.942 --> 30:16.031
Ooh, there you are.

30:16.075 --> 30:17.511
Oh, my sweet boy.

30:17.554 --> 30:20.514
Aww, I was worried sick.

30:20.557 --> 30:22.037
Really?
You were worried sick?

30:22.081 --> 30:23.386
I can't take care of a dog?

30:23.430 --> 30:25.214
Okay, I have no idea
where he came from.

30:25.258 --> 30:26.999
I don't know what
you're capable of anymore.

30:27.042 --> 30:29.044
I know you wanna hurt me.
That much seems clear.

30:29.088 --> 30:30.437
He is my dog too.

30:30.480 --> 30:32.265
Maybe I just missed him.
Did you ever think of that?

30:32.308 --> 30:33.919
Yeah, my lease
doesn't allow pets.

30:33.962 --> 30:36.051
Name one time you've ever gotten
up in the morning to walk him.

30:36.095 --> 30:37.879
Huh?
You can't.

30:37.923 --> 30:39.881
You can't even take care
of yourself.

30:39.925 --> 30:41.143
You're a mess, Roxy.

30:41.187 --> 30:43.102
Okay, Mrs. Doyle,

30:43.145 --> 30:44.973
I know that you are very upset
about losing your dog--

30:45.017 --> 30:47.410
You should stay out of this,
brother humper.

30:47.454 --> 30:50.109
And no, I did not lose my dog.
He was stolen.

30:50.152 --> 30:52.415
You can't steal
your own dog, okay?

30:52.459 --> 30:53.895
Nice try, Diane.

30:53.939 --> 30:55.201
Ugh, just give me the dog.

30:55.244 --> 30:57.333
-No, stop, stop.
-JULIA: Hey, hey, hey, stop.

30:57.377 --> 30:59.248
We need to call a truce here.

30:59.292 --> 31:00.597
Okay?

31:00.641 --> 31:03.035
-Can I have the dog?
-Just be careful.

31:04.863 --> 31:07.300
Okay, I'm guessing little...

31:07.343 --> 31:09.302
BOTH: Mitch Gaylord.

31:09.345 --> 31:10.520
Of course.

31:10.564 --> 31:13.219
I'm guessing little Mitch
might be happier

31:13.262 --> 31:16.918
with his yard
to run around in, right?

31:16.962 --> 31:19.094
And I'm guessing you,
Mrs. Doyle,

31:19.138 --> 31:21.096
are being a little bit more
hurtful than normal

31:21.140 --> 31:22.532
because in addition
to losing your dog,

31:22.576 --> 31:24.926
you also feel like
you're losing your daughter.

31:26.536 --> 31:28.103
Now,

31:28.147 --> 31:31.846
I will give you back the dog
if you promise to

31:31.890 --> 31:33.935
just give Roxy some space.

31:35.110 --> 31:37.286
Because she's...

31:37.330 --> 31:39.201
an adult,

31:39.245 --> 31:42.596
and very capable
of taking care of herself.

31:44.163 --> 31:45.425
Does that seem fair?

31:48.341 --> 31:49.951
None of this is fair.

32:03.965 --> 32:06.533
You okay?

32:06.576 --> 32:08.970
Thanks for sticking up for me.

32:09.014 --> 32:10.189
It's no big deal.

32:11.668 --> 32:13.496
It is.

32:13.540 --> 32:15.281
Sticking up for people
is a big deal.

32:29.643 --> 32:33.168
Listen, I wanna make something
really clear to you, Leon,

32:33.212 --> 32:34.474
before we continue
with anything.

32:34.517 --> 32:36.345
Well, sure.
I mean, you're in charge.

32:37.564 --> 32:39.131
Everything I've done,

32:39.174 --> 32:41.220
I have done on my own.

32:41.263 --> 32:43.004
My career, my accomplishments--

32:43.048 --> 32:45.050
you have no idea
how much harder you have to work

32:45.093 --> 32:46.399
as a young, black woman.

32:46.442 --> 32:48.531
And I will not let you or anyone

32:48.575 --> 32:51.143
undermine me or confuse me.

32:51.186 --> 32:52.274
I know who I am.

32:52.318 --> 32:54.537
And I'm--I'm very proud of you.

32:54.581 --> 32:55.974
EDIE: No.
That's just it.

32:56.017 --> 32:58.541
It's not about you.
You don't get to take credit.

32:58.585 --> 32:59.673
Take credit?

32:59.716 --> 33:01.631
Or--or be proud or whatever.

33:03.068 --> 33:05.200
The Young Leaders Scholarship?

33:05.244 --> 33:06.723
Catchy title.

33:06.767 --> 33:08.247
I didn't win anything.

33:08.290 --> 33:09.465
I wrote a pitch-perfect essay

33:09.509 --> 33:11.554
about Jane Bolin's
first judicial ruling.

33:11.598 --> 33:13.078
Nobody even read it.

33:13.121 --> 33:14.644
I read it.

33:14.688 --> 33:17.952
Yeah, well, I worked my ass off.

33:17.996 --> 33:19.562
-You wrote a check.
-Your mother and I--

33:19.606 --> 33:22.217
You created a bogus scholarship
so that you could participate

33:22.261 --> 33:24.002
so that you could feel good

33:24.045 --> 33:25.742
like you actually had
anything to do with me.

33:25.786 --> 33:28.745
I saw your potential.

33:28.789 --> 33:31.313
You knew what things were like
for me growing up, Leon.

33:31.357 --> 33:33.098
And that's why I wanted to help.

33:33.141 --> 33:34.621
EDIE: I didn't need a handout.

33:36.101 --> 33:37.406
I needed a father.

33:39.452 --> 33:42.498
All those Thanksgivings I sat
across from you, and you knew.

33:44.109 --> 33:46.111
Why didn't you ever tell me
who you really were?

33:48.635 --> 33:51.159
Were you ever gonna tell me?

33:54.510 --> 33:57.252
A lot of people would've
gotten hurt if I had told you.

34:06.305 --> 34:08.350
Mr. Marcus will
be right with you.

34:08.394 --> 34:09.351
Thanks.

34:13.703 --> 34:14.661
Hey.

34:14.704 --> 34:16.358
Hi.

34:16.402 --> 34:18.752
Are you in trouble
'cause of the party?

34:18.795 --> 34:20.188
Did you come
to say you're sorry?

34:20.232 --> 34:22.364
No, I'm here to see you.

34:25.150 --> 34:27.152
Why?

34:27.195 --> 34:29.241
Well, because

34:29.284 --> 34:31.808
you remind me of someone
I know who discovered

34:31.852 --> 34:35.073
they had this superpower
when they were about your age.

34:35.116 --> 34:36.291
Who's that?

34:36.335 --> 34:37.510
Me.

34:39.120 --> 34:41.209
I don't feel like
I have a superpower.

34:41.253 --> 34:42.515
Well, that's just because
you haven't figured out

34:42.558 --> 34:44.517
how to use it yet.

34:44.560 --> 34:46.649
-But I can help you.

34:46.693 --> 34:48.521
-Think you can work hard?
-Yeah.

34:48.564 --> 34:49.696
Okay.

34:50.784 --> 34:53.178
But my mom's just a nanny.

34:53.221 --> 34:55.658
She probably can't pay.

34:55.702 --> 34:57.138
It's okay.
We'll figure something out.

34:57.182 --> 34:59.184
Hit me up on the socials, okay?
Gotta jet.

34:59.227 --> 35:03.101
SINGER: ♪ I believe it's time
for me to fly ♪

35:06.365 --> 35:09.194
SINGERS:
♪ Time for me to fly

35:09.237 --> 35:12.414
SINGER: ♪ Oh,
I've got to set myself free ♪

35:12.458 --> 35:14.416
♪ Time for me to fly

35:14.460 --> 35:16.462
Okay, you ready?

35:18.377 --> 35:20.161
-SAM:
-Here we go.

35:20.205 --> 35:21.858
Okay.

35:21.902 --> 35:24.165
And...

35:24.209 --> 35:26.515
Hi, it's Julia Bechley.

35:26.559 --> 35:28.300
And I'm here with Sam McCormick.

35:28.343 --> 35:29.388
Hi, there.

35:29.431 --> 35:30.389
And we just thought
it was important

35:30.432 --> 35:32.173
to set the record straight.

35:32.217 --> 35:34.741
-This is my brother.
-And this is my sister.

35:34.784 --> 35:37.439
And we did have sex.

35:37.483 --> 35:40.138
-Yep, that happened.
-It did.

35:40.181 --> 35:43.532
Listen, we didn't know
that we were...

35:43.576 --> 35:46.187
When we were...
You get it.

35:46.231 --> 35:48.885
Anyway, ever since
we found out we were related,

35:48.929 --> 35:52.367
our worlds have pretty much
been turned upside down.

35:52.411 --> 35:54.413
It tested us.

35:54.456 --> 35:56.328
Tested me.

35:56.371 --> 35:58.895
Everything I thought
I knew about my life--

35:58.939 --> 36:02.116
who my family was,
what my identity is--

36:02.160 --> 36:04.292
has changed.

36:04.336 --> 36:07.730
I have brothers and sisters
that I didn't even know about

36:07.774 --> 36:10.516
until a couple weeks ago--
tons of them.

36:10.559 --> 36:13.345
And I get wanting to make me
the laughingstock.

36:13.388 --> 36:15.782
I mean,
the #brotherhumper thing?

36:15.825 --> 36:18.393
Genuinely funny.

36:18.437 --> 36:22.397
But I'm a person with feelings.

36:22.441 --> 36:25.313
I know that I have
a lot more family out there.

36:25.357 --> 36:28.621
And I know this isn't
just happening me.

36:28.664 --> 36:30.927
One in ten people has a father

36:30.971 --> 36:32.886
that isn't really
their father.

36:32.929 --> 36:34.714
And these are the people
that I wanna help

36:34.757 --> 36:36.716
'cause you are my family.

36:38.544 --> 36:42.852
Leon Bechley is my father,
but I'm not like him.

36:44.637 --> 36:45.942
You hear me, Dad?

36:45.986 --> 36:47.509
I don't know
if you're watching this,

36:47.553 --> 36:49.772
but if you are,

36:49.816 --> 36:51.470
I'm not you.

36:51.513 --> 36:53.907
I'm honest about who I am.

36:53.950 --> 36:56.518
I'm not hiding.

36:56.562 --> 36:58.564
I'm not going anywhere.

36:58.607 --> 37:00.827
I'm right here.

37:12.273 --> 37:13.840
Wanna burn some sage with that?

37:13.883 --> 37:15.233
'Cause I got some.

37:15.276 --> 37:16.799
-It's tempting.

37:19.019 --> 37:21.369
"Won't deny it.
Still shipping Sam and Julia.

37:21.413 --> 37:23.328
#GrossButIntoIt."

37:23.371 --> 37:25.025
Better to be shipped
than shamed.

37:25.068 --> 37:26.200
Oh, I'll take it.

37:30.204 --> 37:31.118
It worked.

37:31.161 --> 37:33.816
Your crazy, stupid,

37:33.860 --> 37:36.863
dangerous idea
worked like magic.

37:36.906 --> 37:38.081
You saved my sorry ass.

37:38.125 --> 37:41.302
Mm-mm, you saved your sorry ass.
Not me.

37:41.346 --> 37:42.782
And it was weird because
it didn't really seem like

37:42.825 --> 37:44.305
an Isaac idea at all.

37:44.349 --> 37:46.655
You're usually so doctor-y
and conservative,

37:46.699 --> 37:48.178
and all of a sudden,
you're this balls out,

37:48.222 --> 37:50.746
let's-get-in-front-of-it guy.

37:50.790 --> 37:53.314
Someone had to save you
from yourself.

37:53.358 --> 37:54.663
Heard that before.

37:55.969 --> 37:57.144
Thank you.

38:03.193 --> 38:04.804
My grandmother has that sweater.

38:06.109 --> 38:07.372
SINGER:
♪ I've been pulled down

38:07.415 --> 38:09.417
♪ Till I'm deep

38:09.461 --> 38:12.812
♪ Given scars
that will never heal ♪

38:12.855 --> 38:15.162
♪ But I

38:15.205 --> 38:19.688
♪ I'm gonna make it home

38:19.732 --> 38:20.863
JULIA: Hey.

38:20.907 --> 38:23.692
Listen, I--I owe you an apology.

38:25.172 --> 38:27.348
For making a scene.

38:27.392 --> 38:29.829
I know what it feels like

38:29.872 --> 38:31.831
to be exposed,

38:31.874 --> 38:33.833
to feel outed.

38:33.876 --> 38:37.837
And so all the dad stuff aside,

38:37.880 --> 38:39.404
I'm really sorry.

38:42.145 --> 38:45.018
Thank you.

38:45.061 --> 38:47.194
The first thing
I should've asked was...

38:48.848 --> 38:50.850
How are you?

38:50.893 --> 38:52.155
I'm married.

38:52.199 --> 38:54.375
And I love my husband
and my career,

38:54.419 --> 38:56.246
and I'm not gonna
throw it all away.

38:58.988 --> 39:01.121
That's not what I asked.

39:01.164 --> 39:02.862
I know.

39:04.864 --> 39:06.735
Well, I'm--

39:06.779 --> 39:09.347
I'm here if you ever wanna talk.

39:09.390 --> 39:11.871
You know where to find me.

39:11.914 --> 39:13.960
I'm kind of a big deal
on the Internet now.

39:14.003 --> 39:15.309
I don't know if you've heard.

39:15.353 --> 39:17.485
Yeah.

39:17.529 --> 39:20.009
SINGER: ♪ I'll break
these walls out of... ♪

39:20.053 --> 39:21.837
Julia.

39:21.881 --> 39:23.535
SINGER:
♪ I will shake the dust

39:23.578 --> 39:26.189
Thanks--

39:26.233 --> 39:29.758
just for talking to me
like you're my sister,

39:29.802 --> 39:31.238
and not like you're Tim's ex.

39:31.281 --> 39:33.849
SINGER: ♪ I'll be stronger
in the end ♪

39:33.893 --> 39:37.287
♪ I will speak my mind,
I will win the fight ♪

39:37.331 --> 39:39.507
♪ I will face my fears

39:39.551 --> 39:42.945
♪ I will be the light

39:42.989 --> 39:44.425
♪ This heart will mend

39:44.469 --> 39:46.862
♪ Won't break, won't bend

39:46.906 --> 39:48.386
Oh, hey.

39:48.429 --> 39:50.213
Hey.

39:50.257 --> 39:53.086
-Roxy, Julia's sister.
-Yeah, I remember you.

39:53.129 --> 39:55.262
What a coinkydink.
I didn't know you were a runner.

39:55.305 --> 39:57.003
I didn't know
you were a runner either.

39:57.046 --> 40:00.006
Well, you know, I'm an athlete.
I'm a silver medalist.

40:00.049 --> 40:03.836
Oh, so you're a medal dropper?

40:03.879 --> 40:05.533
Well, I'm sorry.
Do you have one?

40:05.577 --> 40:07.405
-Uh-huh.
-Actually, I'm a trainer now.

40:07.448 --> 40:08.928
I just picked up a new client.

40:08.971 --> 40:10.538
Just trying to get my wind up,
you know?

40:10.582 --> 40:12.801
You know, I love this route
because it ends right at Equinox

40:12.845 --> 40:14.455
and then I can just
start my circuit, you know?

40:14.499 --> 40:15.891
Yeah, that's funny because

40:15.935 --> 40:17.937
that's actually
the same workout I do.

40:17.980 --> 40:20.069
Pretty sure I posted it
on my Instagram the other day.

40:20.113 --> 40:21.941
Oh, did you?

40:21.984 --> 40:23.421
Huh.

40:23.464 --> 40:25.118
Hey, so, what do you run?
Like, an eight-minute mile?

40:25.161 --> 40:27.903
-Something like that.
-Okay, let's see what you got.

40:30.340 --> 40:32.560
SINGER: ♪ I'll be stronger
in the end ♪

40:46.313 --> 40:48.141
You're gonna tell me
you can't do this.

40:50.535 --> 40:51.536
Yeah.

40:58.499 --> 41:00.501
So that's it?

41:00.545 --> 41:01.981
We're done?

41:04.374 --> 41:05.463
We're done.

